From: postmarketOS platina porting
Subject: [PATCH] ath10k: do not send WMI set_psmode on WCN3990 (SDM660)

The WCN3990 WLAN firmware (WLAN.HL.1.0.1.c6) running inside the SDM660
modem crashes (EX:wlan_process, PC=b00c75b8) the moment it receives the
WMI set_psmode command. ath10k_mac_vif_setup_ps() sends this command
unconditionally during STA vif bring-up and scan (the "force-enable PS
for non-running vdevs" path), independent of whether SUPPORTS_PS is
advertised. Short-circuit the function for WCN3990 so the crash-
triggering command is never sent and scan/connect can proceed.

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/mac.c	2026-06-10 17:44:36.997156681 -0500
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath10k/mac.c	2026-06-10 17:44:37.018495038 -0500
@@ -1952,6 +1952,16 @@
 
 	lockdep_assert_held(&arvif->ar->conf_mutex);
 
+	/*
+	 * The WCN3990 WLAN firmware on the SDM660 (running inside the modem
+	 * Q6) crashes with EX:wlan_process PC=b00c75b8 as soon as it receives
+	 * the WMI set_psmode command. This command is otherwise sent
+	 * unconditionally during STA vif bring-up / scan. Skip it entirely on
+	 * WCN3990 so the firmware stays alive and scan/connect can proceed.
+	 */
+	if (QCA_REV_WCN3990(ar))
+		return 0;
+
 	if (arvif->vif->type != NL80211_IFTYPE_STATION)
 		return 0;
 
